      • PolyAttribute

        public PolyAttribute(java.lang.String className,
                     java.lang.String identifier,
                     int visibility,
                     boolean mfr_static,
                     boolean mfr_constant,
                     boolean mfr_abstract)
        Constructs a class-typed attribute.

        Sets the class name, identifier, visibility, and modifiers for this attribute. Data type is implicit and is set to PolyDataType.CLASS as the String assumes identifying a non-primitive data type.

        Parameters:
        className - name of the class type
        identifier - name of the attribute
        visibility - visibility of the attribute
        mfr_static - static status of the attribute
        mfr_constant - constant status of the attribute
        mfr_abstract - abstract status of the attribute
        See Also:
        PolyAttribute(PolyDataType, String, int, boolean, boolean, boolean), PolyDataType.PolyDataType(java.lang.String), PolyDataType.CLASS
